    {
      "beat_id": "B02",
      "estimated_duration_s": 11,
      "narration_text": "The harmonic oscillator has a parabolic potential. Solving its differential equation directly works, but the algebra hides the pattern. The smarter move is to rewrite position and momentum as two matched operators.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "accumulate"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B02.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 12.42,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B02.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T13:22:54"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B03",
      "estimated_duration_s": 9,
      "narration_text": "The Hamiltonian can be written as h bar omega times the number operator plus one half. That one line already says energy is counted in identical packets, with a half packet left even at the bottom.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "hold"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B03.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 11.75,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B03.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T13:22:54"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B04",
      "estimated_duration_s": 12,
      "narration_text": "Apply the raising operator to an energy eigenstate. The new state has energy larger by exactly h bar omega. Apply it again: another identical step. The spacing does not depend on which rung you started from.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "accumulate"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B04.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 12.65,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B04.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T13:22:54"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B05",
      "estimated_duration_s": 4,
      "narration_text": "The mechanism: one operator, one quantum, one rung.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "hold"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B05.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 3.75,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B05.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T13:22:54"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B06",
      "estimated_duration_s": 12,
      "narration_text": "The lowering operator runs the movie backward. Each application removes h bar omega. But energy cannot descend forever: at the ground state the lowering operator returns zero. There is no physical rung below it.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "trace"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B06.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 12.37,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B06.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T13:22:54"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B07",
      "estimated_duration_s": 11,
      "narration_text": "That stopping condition fixes the ground-state energy at one half h bar omega. Every other level follows by climbing: three halves, five halves, seven halves, always separated by one h bar omega.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "accumulate"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B07.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 12.37,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B07.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T13:22:54"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B08",
      "estimated_duration_s": 4,
      "narration_text": "The bottom is not zero. The spacing never changes.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "hold"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B08.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 3.73,
